                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-sm-8">

                <h1>Awards and Recognition</h1>
                <p>
                    Most of the personal awards I've received have come due to my company PowerQuest. This was an
                    incredible ride, and I couldn't have done it without some amazing people surrounding me, including
                    my brother Dave and the rest of my wonderful intial team: Robert Raymond, Michael Robertson, Troy Millet, Ron Hammond,
                    and John Christensen.
                </p>
                <p>
                    And our amazing team was added upon many times.  We were able to attract and hire
                    other talented professionals who joined our company... and then became wonderful friends.
                    We would say how grateful we were for such a great situation with WordPerfect and Novell close by:
                    they would find, hire, and train the most incredible talent... then we would steal them and make 'em ours!
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <h2>Intellectual Property</h2>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-sm-8">
                <p>
                    Prior to starting PowerQuest, I wasn't sure about patents and how important they might be. Our counsel,
                    <a target="_blank" href="http://ogilvielawfirm.com/Frame-5-credentialspage5.html?refresh=1310824596743">John Ogilvie</a>,
                    helped me understand that they are important, that they could and would make a difference for us. I'm glad I listened.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Here is a list of @Html.ActionLink("patents issued to me and/or pending", "IP"). Most came from my PowerQuest
                    ideas. The pending ones relate to @Html.ActionLink("NumberGun", "NumberGun").
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

